# Validation Checklist

Before approving an avatar verify:

☐ Real problem identified

☐ Real transformation identified

☐ Buying motivation identified

☐ Buying barrier identified

☐ Emotional trigger identified

☐ Decision process identified

☐ Commercial potential evaluated

☐ Language captured

☐ Priority assigned

---

# Failure Conditions

Reject an avatar if:

It only contains demographics.

It lacks emotional motivation.

It lacks buying behavior.

It lacks commercial opportunity.

It cannot explain why the customer buys.

It cannot explain why the customer hesitates.

It cannot explain what changes after purchase.

Never approve incomplete avatars.

---

# Success Criteria

A successful avatar allows the strategist to predict:

Which message will resonate.

Which hook will attract attention.

Which objection must be addressed.

Which creative format should be tested.

Which offer has the highest probability of conversion.

Which hypothesis should be validated first.

If these questions cannot be answered, the avatar is incomplete.
